19/10/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The government has reportedly agreed with a French proposal to establish an international commission on adoptions.
Prime Minister Adrian Nastase discussed the idea with French counterpart Jean-Pierre Raffarin in Bucharest on Monday (18 October).
According to Raffarin, the proposal applies in particular to the cases of French couples caught in the middle of adoption proceedings by a Romanian moratorium on international adoptions in 2001.
In other news, Parliamentary Assembly of the Council of Europe President Peter Schieder visited Bucharest on Monday and praised the progress achieved by Romania on the road to full EU membership.
(Nine o'clock, Rompres - 19/10/04;
Reuters - 18/10/04)
